AB  - This paper examines the association between block
                                                ownership and market liquidity. Blockholders are
                                                believed to have access to private, value-relevant
                                                information via their roles as monitors of firms'
                                                operations. consistent with this, we find that firms
                                                with greater blockholder ownership, either by
                                                managers or external entities, have larger quoted
                                                spreads, effective spreads, adverse selection spread
                                                components, and smaller quoted depths.
